<div id="review_2680710" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2680710" />
    <a title="Maria Elmvang" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/168347-maria-elmvang"><img alt="Maria Elmvang" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442612167p2/168347.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2680710?book_show_action=true">Jul 03, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria Elmvang" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria Elmvang" href="/user/show/168347-maria-elmvang">Maria Elmvang</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780553258547" href="/book/show/797088.Dragonsinger">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=5-stars">5-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=owned-physical-book">owned-physical-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2011">2011</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2006">2006</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2004">2004</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2008">2008</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/168347-maria-elmvang?shelf=2014">2014</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2680710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3043154541137781069">This is one of those books that would have been too short practically no matter how long it was. One of my very favourite books, and one of my introductions to the fantasy genre. I love the atmosphere it describes, and would love to experience some lessons at Harper Hall myself... even though I&apos;d probably be more likely to be one of the clueless girls (although not as cruel I hope) than Menolly.<br/><br/>I love the lyrics that start off each chapter. Usually when books have lyrics or poems as introduction</span>
  <span id="freeText3043154541137781069" style="display:none">This is one of those books that would have been too short practically no matter how long it was. One of my very favourite books, and one of my introductions to the fantasy genre. I love the atmosphere it describes, and would love to experience some lessons at Harper Hall myself... even though I'd probably be more likely to be one of the clueless girls (although not as cruel I hope) than Menolly.<br /><br />I love the lyrics that start off each chapter. Usually when books have lyrics or poems as introductions to chapters I just skip them, but here they seem an integral part of the book :)<br /><br />It's a shame no more books have been written about Menolly's life at Harper Hall. I was so disappointed with Dragondrums, because I wanted to read more about Menolly - not Piemur.<br /><br />Love this book - just wish it was longer.<br /><br />Reread in 2016: No matter how often I read this book, it's just not long enough!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3043154541137781069" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


