<div id="review_3534959072" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3534959072" />
    <a title="Olga Godim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7438487-olga-godim"><img alt="Olga Godim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442639299p2/7438487.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3534959072?book_show_action=true">Sep 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Olga Godim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Olga Godim" href="/user/show/7438487-olga-godim">Olga Godim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780689860072" href="/book/show/28547.Dragonsinger">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7438487-olga-godim?shelf=fantasy-scifi">fantasy-scifi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3534959072" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13243374493936244554">A nice story. In a way it reminded me of Harry Potter. This is also a school story, but not a magic school. This novel is about a music school in Anne McCaffrey’s fantasy world of Pern. <br/>The narrative is mediocre, and the stakes are low. No saving the world in this book, just one girl with the gift for music trying to find a place for herself. Of all the books by this author I ever tried to read, the only ones that worked for me so far are <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28541.Dragonsong__Harper_Hall___1_' title='Dragonsong (Harper Hall, #1) by Anne McCaffrey' rel='nofollow noopener'>Dragonsong</a> – Menolly’s first story – and this one – Menol</span>
  <span id="freeText13243374493936244554" style="display:none">A nice story. In a way it reminded me of Harry Potter. This is also a school story, but not a magic school. This novel is about a music school in Anne McCaffrey’s fantasy world of Pern. <br />The narrative is mediocre, and the stakes are low. No saving the world in this book, just one girl with the gift for music trying to find a place for herself. Of all the books by this author I ever tried to read, the only ones that worked for me so far are <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28541.Dragonsong__Harper_Hall___1_" title="Dragonsong (Harper Hall, #1) by Anne McCaffrey" rel="nofollow noopener">Dragonsong</a> – Menolly’s first story – and this one – Menolly’s second story. I liked them both because I liked Menolly. She is a charming protagonist, a young female musician in a world where music is supposed to be men’s business. No woman had even been a harper of Pern. But Menolly’s gift demands music, and she follows her heart while navigating the unfamiliar corridors of a music school with its inevitable factions, petty jealousies, and unexpected friends. <br />Overall: I enjoyed this quiet novel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13243374493936244554" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


