<div id="review_3525800951" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3525800951" />
    <a title="Keith  Blodgett " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49383346-keith-blodgett"><img alt="Keith  Blodgett " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1468233570p2/49383346.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3525800951?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Keith  Blodgett " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Keith  Blodgett " href="/user/show/49383346-keith-blodgett">Keith  Blodgett </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780689860072" href="/book/show/28547.Dragonsinger">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3525800951" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7715602402236867050">Menolly is now in the Harper Hall and slowly coming to realize what he &quot;tunings and twiddlings&quot; can really mean to a people in near constant peril. I do get it. Literacy is rare, books and paper rarer still. They&apos;re truly an agrarian society a space faring people fallen almost out of existence. The Harpers and their songs not only teach and entertain but they&apos;re also the news and information services. And there&apos;s something going on behind the scenes. Harpers doing things unexpected. Turning up a</span>
  <span id="freeText7715602402236867050" style="display:none">Menolly is now in the Harper Hall and slowly coming to realize what he "tunings and twiddlings" can really mean to a people in near constant peril. I do get it. Literacy is rare, books and paper rarer still. They're truly an agrarian society a space faring people fallen almost out of existence. The Harpers and their songs not only teach and entertain but they're also the news and information services. And there's something going on behind the scenes. Harpers doing things unexpected. Turning up and learning, nudging, expanding. This is YA literature at its best. As good as any of Heinlein's juveniles from decades before. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7715602402236867050" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


